Subject: [PATCH 1/2] fix: address all identified bugs and add explanatory
 comments
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- SERVER: fix double Ctrl+C delivery in tcp_pty_bash_bridge.c — skip writing
  raw 0x03 to PTY master after SIGINT already sent via kill(); simultaneously
  optimize byte-by-byte writes into chunk writes using memchr, with EINTR
  handling
- SERVER: fix copy-paste comment in tcp_ser_dev_bridge.c (referenced
  tcp_pty_bash_bridge.elf instead of tcp_ser_dev_bridge.elf)
- SERVER: fix memory leak in tcp_fstate_monitor.c split_path() — free dir
  before exit(1) when name malloc fails
- CLIENT: fix uint8_t cdc_itf vs -1 type mismatch in connect_and_setup_pair
  (main.c) — monitoring server was never treated as optional; change type to
  int and handle both the early-NULL and timeout paths
- CLIENT: fix pbuf leak in cdc_tcp_recv (util.c) — call pbuf_free(p) before
  returning ERR_MEM since lwIP transfers ownership on ERR_MEM
- Add explanatory comments throughout all five files

Agent-Logs-Url: https://github.com/blue-wind-25/JxMake/sessions/ec1fd2b1-4276-432c-aeed-44e1b2216a4b

